8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 170, L.D. 375, “An Act to Require the
10 University of Maine School of Law to Provide an Online Degree Program”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, Directing the University of Maine System to Study the Feasibility of Distance
13 Learning Programs at the University of Maine School of Law'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. University of Maine System to study feasibility of distance learning
16 courses at University of Maine School of Law. Resolved: That the University of
17 Maine System shall study the feasibility of expanding the current juris doctor degree
18 program at the University of Maine School of Law to offer distance learning courses and
19 examine providing a new juris doctor degree program that provides 100% distance
20 learning. The feasibility study must include the following:
21 1. The costs of operating the current juris doctor degree program with distance learning
22 courses and the anticipated effect the offering of distance learning courses will have on
23 student enrollment in the program;
24 2. The costs of operating a new juris doctor degree program that provides 100%
25 distance learning courses and the anticipated enrollment of students in such a program;
26 3. The process and costs of the University of Maine School of Law to apply to the
27 American Bar Association for acquiescence, as necessary, to offer a juris doctor degree
28 program with distance learning, whether by expanding the current juris doctor degree
29 program to offer distance learning courses or by providing a new juris doctor degree
30 program that provides 100% distance learning; and
31 4. The anticipated benefits and disadvantages of expanding and operating the current
32 juris doctor degree program to offer distance learning courses and of providing a new juris
33 doctor degree program providing 100% distance learning courses.
34 The University of Maine System shall submit a report detailing its findings, including any
35 suggested legislation, no later than November 4, 2026, to the joint standing committee of
