316 the Legislature having jurisdiction over education matters. The joint standing committee
327 may report out a bill related to the contents of the report to the 133rd Legislature in 2027.'
3 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
4 number to read consecutively.
5 SUMMARY
66 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. The amendment requires the
77 University of Maine System to study the feasibility of expanding the current juris doctor
88 degree program at the University of Maine School of Law to offer distance learning courses
99 and to examine providing a new juris doctor degree program providing 100% distance
1100 learning. The study must consider the costs of operating the current juris doctor degree
1111 program with distance learning courses and the cost of operating a new juris doctor degree
1122 program providing 100% distance learning courses.
13 The University of Maine System must submit a report with its findings, including
14 suggested legislation, by November 4, 2026 to the joint standing committee of the
15 Legislature having jurisdiction over education matters. The joint standing committee may
16 report out a bill related to the contents of the report.
